title: "Framework for the Metaverse"
author: "Matthew Ball"
domain: "matthewball.co"
url: "https://www.matthewball.co/all/forwardtothemetaverseprimer"
pubDate: 2021-08-07
takeaway: "Lays out a definition and framework for the metaverse and why it represents the next major computing and business platform."
---

Matthew Ball’s framework for the metaverse is a rare piece of intellectual rigor in a space too often dominated by hyperactive marketing and vague buzzwords. As a founder and engineer, I appreciate how Ball bypasses science-fiction cliches and treats the metaverse as a fundamental architectural transition in computing. It’s not just about wearing VR headsets; it’s about a persistent, synchronous, and interoperable digital layer that lives alongside our physical reality. This requires solving massive infrastructure, networking, and standards challenges that we are only beginning to grasp.

What excites me most is the concept of true digital interoperability—the idea that data, identity, and assets can move seamlessly across distinct platforms. In our current web ecosystem, platforms are built like walled gardens designed to trap user value. Building a fully realized metaverse requires a shift in how we approach software engineering and business models, prioritizing open protocols and decentralized databases over proprietary silos. It is a long-term engineering challenge that will define the next generation of venture-backed technology.

### What stuck with me

* **Real-time synchronicity**: Achieving a shared, persistent, and concurrent virtual space requires a massive step-function improvement in global network architecture and latency management.
* **Interoperability is paramount**: The ultimate success of the metaverse depends on open data standards and asset portability that challenge traditional closed platform business models.
* **The next computing epoch**: Rather than a brand new technology, the metaverse represents a slow convergence of mobile, cloud, graphics, and network architectures into a unified platform.
